**Determining the New Administrative Unit for "Xã Vĩnh Thạnh"**

Okay, so the user wants to know the current administrative unit for "Xã Vĩnh Thạnh, Thành phố Nha Trang, Tỉnh Khánh Hòa." My approach will be methodical. First, I need to check if there have been any provincial mergers affecting Khánh Hòa. I'll consult `60-NQ/TW`, but it turns out Khánh Hòa remains Khánh Hòa.

Next, I need to dig deeper. I'll search for "Xã Vĩnh Thạnh" specifically within Khánh Hòa, focusing on resolutions related to administrative rearrangements. Looking at the `Other resolutions` section, I'll scan `1667/NQ-UBTVQH15`. Bingo! That confirms it - "Xã Vĩnh Thạnh" is now part of "phường Tây Nha Trang".

Just to be absolutely certain, I'll verify that "phường Tây Nha Trang" actually exists in the `New wards` list and that it's associated with Khánh Hòa. Sure enough: `{"ward_code":"22390","ward_name":"Phường Tây Nha Trang","province_name":"Tỉnh Khánh Hòa"}`. Perfect.

Given the direct and explicit mention of "Xã Vĩnh Thạnh" in the context of the merger, and the subsequent verification, my confidence in this result is extremely high.
